---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout title="Olle Rönn | Projects">
  <section class="hero projects-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Projects</p>

    <h1>Projects</h1>

    <p class="lead">
      A collection of projects that show practical experience in IT infrastructure,
      cybersecurity, cloud, Linux, server environments, system development and
      technical documentation.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Featured projects</p>
      <h2>Projects with concrete results</h2>
      <p>
        Projects that are live, completed or recently updated. The focus is on
        practical results, documentation and links to GitHub.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="project-grid">
      <article class="project-card featured">
        <div class="project-top">
          <span class="tag">Linux · Security Lab</span>
          <span class="project-status completed">v1 Complete</span>
        </div>

        <h3>Secure Homelab</h3>

        <p>
          A practical infrastructure and cybersecurity project where I built,
          secured and documented a small Linux-based server environment.
        </p>

        <p>
  The environment runs Ubuntu Server inside VirtualBox and includes SSH hardening,
  UFW, fail2ban, Docker, Portainer, Uptime Kuma, Homepage and Nginx.
</p>

        <div class="tech-list">
          <span>Ubuntu Server</span>
          <span>VirtualBox</span>
          <span>SSH</span>
          <span>UFW</span>
          <span>fail2ban</span>
          <span>Docker</span>
          <span>Monitoring</span>
        </div>

        <div class="project-actions">
          <a class="project-button" href="/homelab">Read case study</a>
          <a
            class="project-button secondary"
            href="https://github.com/ollernn/secure-homelab"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noreferrer"
          >
            View GitHub
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>

     <article class="project-card featured">
  <div class="project-top">
    <span class="tag">Astro · Portfolio</span>
    <span class="project-status live">Live</span>
  </div>

  <h3>Portfolio Website</h3>

  <p>
    A personal portfolio built with Astro and deployed with Vercel. The site
    presents my projects, CV information, learning logs and technical development
    in a structured way.
  </p>

  <p>
    The project is live and continuously updated as new projects, improvements
    and documentation are added.
  </p>

  <div class="tech-list">
    <span>Astro</span>
    <span>HTML</span>
    <span>CSS</span>
    <span>GitHub</span>
    <span>Vercel</span>
  </div>

  <div class="project-actions">
    <a
      class="project-button"
      href="https://github.com/ollernn/portfolio"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noreferrer"
    >
      View GitHub
    </a>
  </div>
</article>

    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Previous projects</p>
      <h2>Larger previous projects</h2>
      <p>
        Projects from studies and previous work that demonstrate practical
        experience in system development, cloud services, networking, security
        and infrastructure.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="project-list">
      <a
        class="project-row clickable-project"
        href="https://github.com/ollernn/OOPC-VT25-Grupp-07"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noreferrer"
      >
        <div>
          <span class="tag">C# · WPF · MVVM</span>
          <h3>Sport Club Management System</h3>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p>
            A larger C# and WPF project where we built a sport club management
            system with separate views for members, coaches and administrators.
          </p>

          <p>
            The system supports registration, login, booking and cancellation of
            training sessions, profile management, training history, points,
            calories and equipment management.
          </p>

          <p>
            The project was built with MVVM and a layered architecture with
            presentation layer, business layer, data layer and entity layer.
            It used service classes, repositories and Unit of Work for business
            logic and database access.
          </p>

          <div class="tech-list">
            <span>C#</span>
            <span>WPF</span>
            <span>MVVM</span>
            <span>Entity Framework</span>
            <span>SQL Server</span>
            <span>Repository Pattern</span>
            <span>Unit of Work</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </a>

      <article class="project-row">
        <div>
          <span class="tag">IoT · Cloud</span>
          <h3>Smart Security System</h3>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p>
            Designed and implemented a security solution using a camera, sensor
            data and cloud services. The solution used event-driven automation
            where image or video data was connected to door sensor events.
          </p>

          <div class="tech-list">
            <span>Azure</span>
            <span>Home Assistant</span>
            <span>IoT</span>
            <span>Camera</span>
            <span>Sensor</span>
            <span>Automation</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="project-row">
        <div>
          <span class="tag">Infrastructure · IAM</span>
          <h3>Enterprise Network & Active Directory Environment</h3>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p>
            Simulated an enterprise environment with multiple servers and clients.
            The project included users, permissions, policies, Active Directory,
            Group Policy, DHCP, shared resources, firewall rules, redundancy and
            failover.
          </p>

          <div class="tech-list">
            <span>Active Directory</span>
            <span>GPO</span>
            <span>DHCP</span>
            <span>Firewall Rules</span>
            <span>Windows Server</span>
            <span>Failover</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="project-row">
        <div>
          <span class="tag">Cybersecurity</span>
          <h3>Network Traffic & Threat Analysis</h3>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p>
            Analyzed PCAP files in Wireshark to investigate network activity,
            identify suspicious traffic, analyze data exfiltration and interpret
            security-related events.
          </p>

          <div class="tech-list">
            <span>Wireshark</span>
            <span>PCAP</span>
            <span>VirusTotal</span>
            <span>CyberChef</span>
            <span>Threat Analysis</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Learning projects</p>
      <h2>Smaller learning projects</h2>
      <p>
        Smaller projects used to test technologies, understand security concepts
        and build practical experience step by step.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="project-grid compact">
      <a
        class="project-card clickable-project"
        href="https://github.com/ollernn/Security-project"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noreferrer"
      >
        <div class="project-top">
          <span class="tag">Python · Flask · API Security</span>
          <span class="project-status learning">Learning</span>
        </div>

        <h3>Simple API Security Demo</h3>

        <p>
          A smaller Flask project demonstrating how an API endpoint can be
          protected with an API key using request headers and environment variables.
        </p>

        <p>
          The project was used as a learning exercise to understand basic API
          security, environment variable handling and simple access control.
        </p>

        <div class="tech-list">
          <span>Flask</span>
          <span>API Keys</span>
          <span>Environment Variables</span>
          <span>Access Control</span>
        </div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Future projects</p>
      <h2>Planned project areas</h2>
      <p>
        Ideas that can be developed further as the portfolio grows with more
        technical projects and documentation.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="project-grid planned-grid">
      <article class="project-card">
        <div class="project-top">
          <span class="tag">Cloud · Azure</span>
          <span class="project-status planned">Planned</span>
        </div>

        <h3>Secure Azure Environment</h3>

        <p>
          A future Azure environment focused on IAM, logging, monitoring, storage,
          cost control and cloud security.
        </p>

        <div class="tech-list">
          <span>Azure</span>
          <span>Entra ID</span>
          <span>IAM</span>
          <span>Logging</span>
          <span>Cloud Security</span>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="project-card">
        <div class="project-top">
          <span class="tag">Monitoring · Security</span>
          <span class="project-status planned">Planned</span>
        </div>

        <h3>Monitoring / Mini-SOC Dashboard</h3>

        <p>
          A future project focused on logging, monitoring, alerts and dashboards
          from local systems, cloud resources or lab environments.
        </p>

        <div class="tech-list">
          <span>Grafana</span>
          <span>Prometheus</span>
          <span>Logs</span>
          <span>Alerts</span>
          <span>Security Monitoring</span>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  .projects-hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 5.2vw, 4.2rem);
  }

  .project-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .project-grid.compact {
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr);
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .planned-grid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
  }

  .project-card,
  .project-row {
    background:
      linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.035), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.015)),
      var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1.35rem;
    transition:
      transform 160ms ease,
      border-color 160ms ease,
      background 160ms ease;
  }

  .project-card:hover,
  .project-row:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    border-color: var(--border-hover);
    background:
      linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.045), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02)),
      var(--surface-soft);
  }

  .project-card.featured {
    border-color: var(--border-hover);
  }

  .clickable-project {
    display: block;
    color: inherit;
    text-decoration: none;
    cursor: pointer;
  }

  .clickable-project h3 {
    transition: color 160ms ease;
  }

  .clickable-project:hover h3 {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .project-top {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .project-status {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    width: fit-content;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.55rem;
    border-radius: 999px;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .project-status.live {
    background: rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.12);
    color: #86efac;
  }

  .project-status.active {
    background: rgba(147, 197, 253, 0.14);
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .project-status.completed {
    background: rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.12);
    color: #cbd5e1;
  }

  .project-status.planned {
    background: rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.12);
    color: #d8b4fe;
  }

  .project-status.learning {
    background: rgba(250, 204, 21, 0.12);
    color: #fde68a;
  }

  .project-list {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .project-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(220px, 0.65fr) minmax(0, 1.35fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .tech-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.45rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .tech-list span {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    width: fit-content;
    padding: 0.28rem 0.58rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 999px;
    color: var(--text-soft);
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.025);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 650;
  }

  .project-actions {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
  }

  .project-button {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  width: fit-content;
  padding: 0.5rem 0.85rem;
  border-radius: 999px;
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.025);
  color: var(--text-soft);
  font-size: 0.82rem;
  font-weight: 800;
  text-decoration: none;
  transition:
    color 160ms ease,
    border-color 160ms ease,
    background 160ms ease,
    transform 160ms ease;
}

.project-button:hover {
  color: var(--accent);
  border-color: var(--border-hover);
  background: rgba(147, 197, 253, 0.08);
  transform: translateY(-1px);
}

.project-button.secondary {
  color: var(--text-soft);
  border-color: var(--border);
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.025);
}

.project-button.secondary:hover {
  color: var(--accent);
  border-color: var(--border-hover);
  background: rgba(147, 197, 253, 0.08);
}

  code {
    color: var(--accent);
    background: rgba(147, 197, 253, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(147, 197, 253, 0.14);
    padding: 0.08rem 0.28rem;
    border-radius: 0.35rem;
    font-size: 0.9em;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .project-grid,
    .planned-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .project-row {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 0.75rem;
    }

    .project-top {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>